title: Training and Development Specialist/Team Lead
description: Plans, prepares, coordinates, and presents formal instruction to 344th Military Intelligence Battalion soldiers. Develops and supervises implementation of Programs of Instruction (POI) and lesson plans to ensure curriculum meets training requirements, budget constraints, and intelligence-related language needs. Conducts formal classroom training, demonstrations, practical exercises, and computer assisted instruction. Analyzes course content to meet mission, time, and language needs. Validates technical training instruction, curriculum, and resourcing. Provides instruction on intelligence collection, reporting vehicles and formats, DOD and US intelligence agencies, analog and digital equipment instruction, and signal processing techniques. Ensures Non-Target Cryptologic Linguist Instructors meet language and educational requirements to teach. • Specially chosen as personal assistant to Korean Cryptologic Course Supervisor at 2012 Critical Task Site Selection Board (CTSSB) for MOS 35P to ensure Critical Task Lists (CTL) were updated to match intelligence and language training requirements. • Solely rewrote and developed the Korean Cryptologic Linguist course to more closely match intelligence requirements based on mission reporting, activity, and specific threats to US Forces in Korea (USFK). • Trains others on the use of intelligence systems, ArcGIS, DCGS-A, Pathfinder, Microsoft Office Suite, Digital Receiver Technology (DRT), User Interface Services (UIS), Hybrid, Semester, Beamer, Hotzone, and Multi-Function Work Station (MFWS) to create intelligence products. • Go-To-Guy and Subject Matter Expert on course related issues, development, and student records by the Customer, Course Supervisor, Training Development Element (TDE), and other team members. • Created and supervised a project to develop and implement a final Capstone exercise based on the current Guardrail Common Sensor (GR/CS) System, utilizing COMINT, ELINT, and SIGINT reporting procedures.
